PROBLEM STATEMENT

Online fashion shopping has grown rapidly, but customers still face significant challenges in selecting the correct clothing size.
Most existing virtual try-on systems focus only on showing how a garment looks on a person and do not accurately predict whether it will fit properly.
As a result, customers often experience uncertainty regarding size, fitting, and overall appearance, leading to high return rates and dissatisfaction.
Current solutions either require manual body measurements or specialized scanning equipment, making them inconvenient for everyday users.
This project aims to develop an AI-based system that can estimate key body measurements such as shoulder width, chest size, waist size, and arm length from user images.
The estimated measurements can then be used to provide personalized size recommendations and improve confidence in online clothing purchases.
The goal is to make online fashion shopping more accurate, convenient, and reliable.
